<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<h1 style="margin-top:10%">Users</h1>

  <p>This webpage stands as a compelling demonstration crafted through the utilization of Node.js/Express.js and EJS templates. It masterfully presents the list/view design pattern, seamlessly extracting and organizing data from a JSON file. The captivating images and engaging content showcased on the page are ingeniously curated through third-party APIs, portraying entirely fictitious entities to ensure absolute privacy and anonymity.</p>
<p>Moreover, a noteworthy feature of this demo is the enhanced user experience it offers. By clicking on a user's name, visitors are seamlessly navigated to a dedicated page brimming with comprehensive details about the selected user. This insightful addition provides a deeper understanding of the fictional profiles, enriching the overall experience of exploring the demo.</p>

 <table class="table table-hover table-striped">
	<thead>
   	<tr>
      	<th scope="col">First Name</th>
      	<th scope="col">Last Name</th>
      	<th scope="col">Email</th>
   	</tr>
	</thead>
 <tbody>

<% users.forEach(function(user){ %>
  <tr>
   	<td><a href="users/view/<%= user.id %>"><%= user.first_name %></a></td>
   	<td><%= user.last_name %></td>
   	<td><%= user.email %></td>
  </tr>
<% }); %>

</tbody>
</table>

